Angry Heroes Game
Project Overview
Angry Heroes is a Java-based game developed using the LibGDX framework. This project includes various levels, sprites, and mechanics for an interactive gaming experience.

How to Run the Game
Prerequisites
Install Java Development Kit (JDK) (Version 8 or above).
Install a compatible Integrated Development Environment (IDE) like IntelliJ IDEA, Eclipse, or any text editor with Gradle support.
Ensure Gradle is installed on your machine (if not bundled in your IDE).

Steps to Run the Game
Open the project in your IDE.
Run the Lwjgl3Launcher class as a Java application.
The game window should launch successfully.

